// diagramType: flowchart-diagram
// Rendered with the eraser-diagrams skill (Eraser /render). Regenerate: feed this DSL to the Eraser MCP and export PNG (imageQuality 3, theme light).
title Loop engineering: the closed-loop /ship runner
direction down
colorMode pastel
typeface clean

Start [shape: oval, color: green, icon: play, label: "Start tools/loop.sh: prompt list, headless claude -p, ultracode"]
Pace [shape: diamond, color: blue, icon: clock, label: "Pacing?"]
Fixed [icon: clock, color: blue, label: "/loop 5m: fixed interval"]
Auto [icon: repeat, color: blue, label: "/loop without interval: model self-paces"]
Run [icon: package, color: blue, label: "Run next prompt then /ship (gate-01 pre-approved in the prompt file)"]
Contract [shape: diamond, color: orange, icon: shield, label: "Completion contract: ratchet ok, floor non-decreasing, tree clean, no secret, CI on main green"]
Checkpoint [icon: save, color: blue, label: "Checkpoint .shipboard/loop-checkpoint.md"]
More [shape: diamond, color: blue, icon: list, label: "More prompts?"]
Halt [shape: oval, color: red, icon: alert-octagon, label: "HALT to owner with the failing reason"]
Done [shape: oval, color: green, icon: check, label: "Post-loop: /cas-audit, codex second opinion, curate journal"]

Start > Pace
Pace > Fixed
Pace > Auto
Fixed > Run
Auto > Run
Run > Contract
Contract > Halt: any condition fails [color: red]
Contract > Checkpoint: all hold [color: green]
Checkpoint > More
More > Run: yes [color: green]
More > Done: no [color: green]
